    <string name="about_text" formatted="false">
        Charlotte Cunningham designed BlabberTabber and created many of the graphics.\n
        \nBrendan Cunnie and Brian Cunnie coded BlabberTabber.\n
        \nDaniel Di Matteo wrote the first android diarization program. His code
        helped us tremendously, and uses LIUM.\n
        \nLIUM is a Java-based open source toolkit for diarization, written by
        Sylvain Meignier, Gregor Dupuy, Paul Gay, and others. It uses Sphinx.\n
        \nCMU Sphinx is open source toolkit for speech recognition.\n
        \nGerald Friedland, Ph.D. and Ekaterina Gonina, Ph.D. advised us and
        published the research papers which inspired us to write BlabberTabber.
        </string>

